olive oil
1 packet freekeh
3.5 cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
2 parsnip
1 onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 bag salad leaves
½ lemon
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
½ tbs honey
1 packet mint
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Rinse the freekeh. In a large
saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add the freekeh
and toast until fragrant, 2 minutes. Add the water and vegetable stock
powder. Bring to the boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until tender,
30-35 minutes. Drain the freekeh and return to the saucepan. Cover to keep
warm and set aside.

While the freekeh is cooking, cut the parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Slice the
red onion into wedges. Divide the peeled & chopped pumpkin, parsnip,
onion and chermoula spice blend over two lined oven trays. Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, roughly chop the spinach & rocket mix. Zest
the lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Roughly chop the roasted
almonds. In a small bowl, combine the dill & parsley mayonnaise with a
dash of water. Set aside. In a second small bowl, combine the honey, lemon
zest, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season and
mix well.

